SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 1262
By Southerland
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Brynn Smith upon
being named to the South Atlantic Conference
Carolinas All-Conference Second Team.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should recognize and
commend those successful student athletes who, through their magnificent exploits, bring honor
to Tennessee and serve as exceptional ambassadors of this State; and
WHEREAS, Brynn Smith of Tusculum University is one such estimable individual, an
athlete of extraordinary talent, skill, and dedication, who has proven herself a formidable
competitor on the beach volleyball court; and
WHEREAS, in recognition of her athletic excellence, Brynn Smith was recently named to
the South Atlantic Conference Carolinas (SACC) All-Conference Second Team after enjoying
an outstanding season with the Tusculum University Pioneers; and
WHEREAS, a native of Wellsburg, Iowa, Ms. Smith earned all-conference honors last
year, as well, earning first-team recognition as a member of Tusculum's top flight; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Smith and her teammate Sylvia Liszewski went 5-7 for the season and
4-2 in SACC play; they led their team through a demanding schedule, contributing to multiple
conference victories and demonstrating consistency, determination, and teamwork throughout
the season; and
WHEREAS, Brynn Smith epitomizes all that is good in today's student athletes, as she
has achieved a high level of success in sports while evincing great character both on and off the
court; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Smith's notable achievement is a source of great pride for her family,
her school, and the State of Tennessee, and it is appropriate that we recognize this
accomplished athlete; now, therefore,
SJR1262
018577
- 1 -

BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we hereby honor and congratulate Brynn Smith
upon being named to the South Atlantic Conference Carolinas All-Conference Second Team,
extending to her our best wishes for continued success in all her future endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
- 2 - 018577

